[SN]TITLE[SN]
Female car driver killed in crash with coal lorry in Thankerton

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 45-year-old woman has died after her car was involved in a crash with a coal lorry in South Lanarkshire.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The incident happened at about 07:40 on the A73 at Thankerton.
An 18-year-old female passenger in the dead woman's Citroen Berlingo was taken to Wishaw General Hospital and later released following treatment for minor injuries.
The 56-year-old lorry driver was also treated for minor injuries. Police have appealed for witnesses.
